Multiplying Powers



                  When multiplying powers, add the powers. 






x^a \times x^b = x^{a+b}



x^4 \times x^6 = x^{4+6} = x^{10}
4x^3 \times 3x^2 = (4 \times 3)x^{3+2} = 12x^5
Powers of Powers



                  When exponentiating a power, multiply the powers. 






(x^a)^b = x^{ab}
